Privacy Policy for Citronus
Thank you for using Citronus. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your data. This privacy policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and what rights you have regarding your personal data.

1. Information We Collect
When you use Citronus, we may collect the following information:

User and Server IDs: We collect this information to provide personalized features and server-specific functionalities, such as commands, ranking, and configuration settings.
Message Data: Citronus may temporarily store message data when using specific commands to ensure the proper functioning of features.
Configuration Preferences: For each configuration command, we record preferences to ensure the bot functions correctly. This data is not shared with anyone and is not read by anyone.
2. Information Collected for the Premium Version
For users of the premium version of Citronus, we collect only the user ID and/or server ID to manage subscriptions and premium features. We do not collect any banking or financial information.

3. How We Use the Information
We use the information collected for the following purposes:

To provide, operate, and maintain the features and services of Citronus.
To customize your experience and offer server-specific configurations.
To store premium subscription data and manage user preferences related to premium features.
To ensure the proper functioning of configuration features by saving user preferences.
To enhance security and monitor for suspicious activities.
4. Data Storage and Security
All collected data is securely stored and accessible only to authorized personnel. We use appropriate measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse.

5. Data Sharing with Third Parties
We do not share or sell your personal data to third parties. The data collected by Citronus is used solely to provide and improve our services. However, if necessary, we may disclose data to comply with legal obligations or cooperate with authorities.

6. User Rights
You have the following rights regarding your data:

Access and Correction: You may request access to the data collected by Citronus and request corrections if any data is inaccurate.
Deletion: You may request the deletion of your data, but please note that this may affect your ability to use certain features of Citronus.
Opt-Out: You may refuse any data collection that is not essential to the bot's operation.
7. Limitation of Liability Clause
By using the premium version of Citronus, you agree not to initiate legal action against the agencies or individuals related to Citronus, including but not limited to developers, administrators, or partners of Citronus. Use of the premium service is at your own risk.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this privacy policy or how your data is handled, you can contact us via our official Discord server: https://discord.gg/9RdU6MYeMs

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be communicated via our official Discord server or other appropriate channels. By continuing to use Citronus after changes, you accept the revised policy.
